#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:1
msgid "E0041"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:3
msgid "Warning name: `missing_rest_mark`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:5
msgid "Closed map pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:7
msgid ""
"MoonBit's map pattern syntax does not support closed pattern (i.e. "
"asserting that the map does not contain any other unmatched elements). So"
" map patterns must always contain a `..`, otherwise this warning will be "
"reported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:11
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:12
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"fn f(map : Map[String, Int]) -> Bool {\n"
"  match map {\n"
"    // the pattern still matches \n"
"    // if `map` contain elements other than \"x\" and \"y\"\n"
"    { \"x\": x, \"y\": y } => true\n"
"    _ => false\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"test {\n"
"  inspect(f({ \"x\": 1, \"y\": 2, \"z\": 3 }), content=\"true\")\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:16
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:17
msgid ""
"If the intended semantic is open matching (i.e. allow existence of "
"unmatched elements), just add `..` to the map pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:19
msgid "If the intended semantic is closed matching, use pattern guard instead:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0041.md:20
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"fn f(map : Map[String, Int]) -> Bool {\n"
"  match map {\n"
"    { \"x\": x, \"y\": y, .. } if map.length() == 2 => true\n"
"    _ => false\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"test {\n"
"  inspect(f({ \"x\": 1, \"y\": 2, \"z\": 3 }), content=\"false\")\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

